import math

def power_num(num, div):
    i = 0
    tmp = div
    while num % div == 0:
        div = div * tmp
        i = i + 1
    return i

    div5 = power_num(i, 5)
    div2 = power_num(i, 2)
    if div5 <= div2:
        ans.append(i)
    else:
        p = math.ceil((div5 - div2) / 2)
        ans.append(i * 4 ** p)
for i in ans:

    tempx = x
